	abstract = {Premise of research. Selection on floral traits by pollinators is expected to play a key role in the diversification of floral phenotypes and the maintenance of species boundaries in sympatry. However, relatively few studies have tested the generality of these assumptions in natural systems, and fewer still have examined multiple phenotypes to better understand which ones are most important to pollinators.

